                            <comment id="12798178" author="stack" created="Fri, 8 Jan 2010 20:56:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Locks being done in wrong order.   This patch should fix it.   Testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12798253" author="stack" created="Fri, 8 Jan 2010 23:38:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To reproduce &amp;#8211; from J-D &amp;#8211; run in standalone mode (I couldn&apos;t repro on cluster).  After reproducing on first run, after application of this patch, hang hasn&apos;t happened after trying sequentialWrite 4 times.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12798265" author="jdcryans" created="Sat, 9 Jan 2010 00:27:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also tried the patch a couple of times and the deadlock is gone. I&apos;m committing the patch to branch plus I removed some annoying debug (MemStoreScanner) that was also added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2037&quot; title=&quot;Alternate indexed hbase implementation; speeds scans by adding indexes to regions rather secondary tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2037&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2037&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
